TY  - JOUR
T1  - Mortgages and Markov Chains: A Simplified Evaluation Model
AU  - Zipkin, Paul
Y1  - 1993/06/01
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.39.6.683
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.39.6.683
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 683
EP  - 691
VL  - 39
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper has two purposes. The first is purely expository: to introduce stochastic interest-rate models and security-evaluation methods in a simple mathematical setting. Specifically, we assume the uncertainties in the model are represented by a discrete-time, finite-state Markov chain. Second, using this framework, we present a relatively simple model for the evaluation of mortgage-backed securities.
AB  - This paper has two purposes. The first is purely expository: to introduce stochastic interest-rate models and security-evaluation methods in a simple mathematical setting. Specifically, we assume the uncertainties in the model are represented by a discrete-time, finite-state Markov chain. Second, using this framework, we present a relatively simple model for the evaluation of mortgage-backed securities.
